com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document

Class SpenObjectContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenObjectBase
      • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenObjectContainer

  • public final class SpenObjectContainer
extends SpenObjectBase
    Class for Contained objects.
    ObjectContainer has the basic object properties by inherit the ObjectBase,
    and has additional features for contained object.

      • setRect

        public void setRect(RectF rect,
           boolean regionOnly)
        Set the specified rectangle of the region.
        ObjectContainer ignores the regionOnly parameter if it is true. because the region of ObjectContainer is determined by the union rectangle of the contained objects.
        If regionOnly parameter is false, all of contained objects should be moved or resized.
        Overrides:
        setRect in class SpenObjectBase
        Parameters:
        rect - The rectangle of the region.
        regionOnly - Set to true to not change the internal data.

      • setUngroupEnabled

        public void setUngroupEnabled(boolean enable)
        Enable or disable the ungroupability of the objects. Default value is true
        Even if this is set to false, you can ungroup the container by calling the SpenPageDoc.ungroupObject(SpenObjectContainer, boolean).
        It just has an influence on authoring of CanvasView.
        Parameters:
        enable - Set to true to enable the ungroupability of the objects.
